A classic thread that gives a mature and responsible consideration of such things as ecosystem and tooling. In particular appreciate Mikera&rsquo;s answer respecting Java&rsquo;s extensibility as the more open of the two, which has led to things like Groovy, Scala, and Clojure (though Clojure also has a CLR version, it&rsquo;s being hosted on the JVM is one of its super-powers).
